---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HomeHero from '../components/HomeHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home">
  <HomeHero />

  <section class="content-card">
    <h2 class="section-heading section-heading-icon">
      <span class="section-heading-mark" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" focusable="false">
          <path d="M12 3.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1 4.5 4.5c0 2.49-2.01 4.5-4.5 4.5S7.5 10.49 7.5 8 9.51 3.5 12 3.5Z" />
          <path d="M4.5 20.5a7.5 7.5 0 0 1 15 0" />
        </svg>
      </span>
      <span>Biography</span>
    </h2>
    <p>
      Rohit Dureja is a computer scientist specializing in formal methods, model checking, and hardware
      verification. He works at <a class="inline-arrow-link" href="https://www.amd.com/">
        AMD<span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
      </a> in Austin on formal verification of microprocessor designs, scalable
      verification flows, and industrial CPU verification tooling.
    </p>
    <p>
      Previously, he worked at <a class="inline-arrow-link" href="https://www.ibm.com/">
        IBM<span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
      </a> on formal hardware verification algorithms and model-checking engines for industrial
      applications.
    </p>
    <p>
      He received his Ph.D. in Computer Science from
      <a class="inline-arrow-link" href="https://www.iastate.edu/">
        Iowa State<span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
      </a>. His doctoral thesis focused on scalable model checking for large design spaces. He also holds a
      master's degree in Embedded Systems from
      <a class="inline-arrow-link" href="https://www.upenn.edu/">
        Penn<span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
      </a>
      and a bachelor's degree in Control Engineering from
      <a class="inline-arrow-link" href="https://www.du.ac.in/">
        Delhi University<span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
      </a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
